Juliana Taiwo-Obalonye, Abuja Former Head of State, General Abdulsalami Abubakar, has said former President Goodluck Jonathan as the reason Nigeria is enjoying peace today. In his remarks at Jonathan‘s book, ‘My Transition Hours’, presentation at the Congress Hall of the hotel, Abubakar described the former president as an example to Africa. He said, “We cannot thank you enough for the peace we are enjoying in the country when you honorably conceded defeat after the 2015 general elections. “Your have remained an example to Africa. You have shown you love your country more than you love power. “I wish you well and wish you many happy returns.” 